Mateo_LeFou writes "Gulf News has a nice piece [0]exposing the last
couple generations of Apple's DRM strategy (you didn't really think they
were abandoning DRM, did you?). Article focuses on how quickly the
tactics are worked around, and how nasty the latest one is: purchased
iTunes now have your personal data in them. Author suspects that this is
to prevent you uploading them to a network."

